text: Danielle Huskisson (born 27 March 1993) is a British swimmer, specialising in open water events. She competed in the women's 10 km event at the 2019 World Aquatics Championships and she finished in 25th place. ==References== Category:1993 births Category:Living people Category:British female swimmers Category:Place of birth missing (living people) Category:Female long-distance swimmers
